V1.0  End of March 1995
-----------------------

We released Cybergames on Aminet and on our Ftp site,
and started to spread it on different BBS's.
We also sent copies to major computer magazines and
PD distributors in England.



V1.01, May 1995
---------------

Of course there had to be problems (Aren't there always?!)
In the hurry to get v1.0 spread, we forgot to include a
text in the Aminet version of how to install the game.
This version included that text. Everything was slowed
down considerably by the fact that we didn't have any
access to Aminet ourselves.



V1.2, October 29th 1995  
-----------------------

-New joystick routine!
-New two player mode!
-Complete version of the game with all the 35 levels on
 three disks. Game Over/You Win included etc etc etc
 (Also included: some things to make you register ;)
-You can see ALL the things in the shop instead of only
 the ones that you can afford!
-Restore-energy object to fall down from the sky!
-More difficult to beat the opponents. Many complained
 that we had made it far to easy.
-"Please insert savedisk" has been changed to
 "Insert savedisk or press ESC"!
-Some minor bugs (Which I'm too embarased to mention)
 has been removed.
-Instructions written for AmigaGuide or Multiview.
-Foolproof (?) Installer scripts written for Amiga
 installer program.



We would like to know what YOU think about this game!
It's better that we get some negative feedback instad of
no feedback at all.
We also would like you to register so that we feel it
was worth while making this game.

