~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 What is Cyberpunk Developments?

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

CPD is a Swedish team. It consists of Bjorn Fogelberg (26)
and Johan Lundin (26). CPD was formed in 1991 when we were
unemployed and had lots of time for making things on
our computers. Before that we were original members
of XAKK, a well known demogroup on the Commodore 64 in
1986-1990. Bjorn was called Knatter and Johan was called
Black Adder.

We started working on Cybergames in December 1991 and
had a preview finished about 6 months later. We both
loved the old game Barbarian and wanted to make something
better with the idea. We managed to find a distributing
company from England which would do all the marketing
and selling of the game. Before the contracts was signed,
they backed as we didn't accept a lousy agreement.
Then the work on the game was down for a long time as
we had lost faith in the whole thing.
One day we were contacted by a new company which we recived
a very good contract from. However things didn't work out
well for the (Swedish) company and they went bankrupt
a couple of months after the Amiga crash in 1994.

After a lot of dispair, quitting and then continuing on
the work of Cybergames, we finally released it as
shareware in March 1995. We figured it was better that
YOU would get a chance to play what we had been working
on for so long, than just putting it aside to forget.

It went pretty well. Some guys loved the game, (like Amiga
Format :) ,and some guys just hated it (like Amiga Power :(
Anyway I don't regret that we released it. It would probably
haunt me forever if we hadn't.

