Cybergames was designed to run on ALL Amigas.
It has been tested with various hardware
and SHOULD work on ALL Amigas from WB 1.2 and
upwards including AGA, ECS and whathaveyou...
However, since I have a crappy job and can't afford
to buy better hardware and actually don't
have any friends left with Amigas to test the
game on, I really don't know...

Cybergames needs 1 meg of memory to run. You can
run it if you have 512 k chip and 512 k fast.

Even as it was designed for PAL computers, it will
work fine on NTSC as well, since there is a built
in feature which handles that.

If it DOESN'T work on your system, please let me
know by sending me a postcard or E-mail. Please try
to be specific to what exactly happened and what
kind of computer you have.


