\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/\/



FIRST OF ALL: INSTALL THE GAME!
Then read on:


Before you run the game,
make sure that you have turned off any program you might
have running in the background.


Start the game.

Now the game will load and you will soon see and hear the
first intro which presents the programmers and some fancy
graphics. When the intro is finished, the main intro will
be loaded.

Before the main intro starts, there will be a requester
which asks you if you want to load your own highscores or
use the default. To use your own hiscores, insert the
disk named Cybergames_savedisk (in any drive, of course)
if you are running from disk.
Otherwise Cybergames_savedisk is assigned to your Cybergames
library.
If there are any hiscores, they will be loaded and used in
the game.
If you want to use the default highscores, just press the
ESC button on the keyboard to continue.


SECOND INTRO

When you are in the second intro, press fire to leave the
credits scroll. Now use the joystick to choose one or two
players, difficulty level, game over on/off and which
background to play if two players have been chosen. Move
to BATTLE and press fire to load the game.
